 0452:     ####Old-Middle River Rule################################################################################################
 0453: 	#The delta pumps make the old-middle river run backwards - there are restrictions (starting in 2008) about how big the negative flows can
 0454: 	#become.  To model this, we use either a liner adjustment of flow at vernalis, or the observed flow (adding back in the pumping, to estimate
 0455: 	#the 'natural' flow on the Old-Middle Rivers).  Once we have a model of the Old-Middle River, we assume that this flow is reduced (can become negative)
 0456: 	# by 90% of the total pumping.  So, if the OMR limit is -5000CFS, & the natural flow is 1000CFS, pumping can be, maximum, 6000CFS/0.9
